This paper discusses the impact of data quality on neural machine translation systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes solutions using scripts, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses identifying and removing problematic sentences, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses the impact of data quality on models.
